I"_<h3 id="the-book">The Book</h3>
<p>This book, written by Swami Harshananda, is available
<a href="https://istore.chennaimath.org/product/modern-problems-and-ancient-solutions/">here</a>.</p>

<h3 id="summary">Summary</h3>
<p>In this book Swami Harshananda starts by showing the problems faced by the
modern society. Later, he suggests an ‘instant pill’ as a solution to these
problems.</p>
<ol>
  <li><em>Satyam Vada. Dharmam Chara.</em> (Speak truth always and act righteously).</li>
  <li>Keeping our bodies fit through proper food and exercise</li>
  <li>Acquiring enough professional competence</li>
  <li>Do nothing in excess</li>
  <li>Improving our intellect by studying philosophy, logic or social sciences</li>
  <li>Developing a sense of appreciating art-forms</li>
  <li>Praying and meditating everyday</li>
  <li>Practising the three principles of life
    <ul>
      <li><em>ahimsa and daya</em> (non-violence and compassion)</li>
      <li><em>asteya and aparigraha</em> (non-greediness and contentment)</li>
      <li><em>brahmacharya</em> (controlling of base passions)</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>
